50|$|A chamber reamer is a {{specific}} type of <b>fluted</b> <b>reamer</b> used by gunsmiths and firearms manufacturers to cut the chamber of a handgun, rifle, or shotgun. The chamber reamer is inserted into the bore of a barrel and held stationary while the barrel is turned around it (typically by means of a lathe). The reamer slowly cuts away material, leaving a chamber capable of accepting {{a specific}} cartridge.|$|E

